    науке, технике. Сер. &quot;Физкультура и спорт&quot;, №3</font></p>
    <p ALIGN="CENTER">&nbsp;</p>
    <p ALIGN="CENTER"><a name="Eng"></a><strong><font size="2">THE INVESTIGATION OR THE
    SUBSTANCE OF TRYIODTYRONYN, TYROXYN AND TYREOTROPYN IN BLOOD SERUM WHILE DOING THE ASAN OF
    HATHA-YOGA</font></strong></p>
    <p ALIGN="CENTER"><font size="2">K.Krapivina, H.Musienko</font></p>
    <p ALIGN="CENTER"><font size="2">Lviv State University,<br>
    Lviv,Ukraine</font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2">Presently the question about the results of the accident
    on the Chernobyl nuclear station is very actual.As it is known,the number of different
    diseases of the thyroid gland increased.Physical exercises of Hatha-yoga have an influence
    on different organs,improving their activity.Right carrying out and using the exercises of
    Hatha-yoga improves the state of health and helps in the treatment of different
    diseases,including the effective influence on the thyroid gland. Eight most popular and
    simple for doing asans were investigated.</font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2">The blood tests were done before the doing the asan and
    while it was being done for eight minutes and after the rest to determine the substance of
    the thyroid gland’s hormons. The determination of tryiodtyronyn, tyroxyn and tyreotropyn
    in blood serum was fulfiled by radioimmunological method.Ten students (girls) of the
    University in the third phase of varial-menstrual cycle,aged 18-20 took part in the
    investigation.</font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2">The tests showed that the level of tyroxyn increases
    only after the pose of Snake has been done,but it increases only to 7-10%.While doing the
    pose of Plough it doesn&quot;t change and after the other exercises are done,increases to
    10-15%.The level of tryiodtyronyn increases after doing the pose of Snake and the level of
    tyroxyn as well.After doing the pose of Lotos it doesn&quot;t change and falls strongly
    enough after doing the Plough,set on the shoulder-blades,the pose of Hero lieing and
    asan,which are to twist the spine.</font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2">The results are not according to the facts of methodical
    literature.For example,many authors point out that the pose of Plough stimulates the
    activity of the thyroid gland and our facts indicate the opposite influence of the pose on
    the activity of this organ.As regards the pose of Snake,there are discords in liliterary
    resources. A.N.Zubkov, A.P.Ochakovsky point out the stimulate effect of this pose on the
    gland.Others say about the opposite influence.Our facts indicate that this is the only of
    the investigated poses,which stimulates the activity of the thyroid gland.</font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2">The influence of poses for twisting the spine,Lotos and
    Hero lieing on the thyroid gland hasn&quot;t been described in methodical literature.As
    regards our results,the pose of Hero lieing oppresses the activity of the thyroid gland
    very much and after staying in this pose the level of tryiodtyronyn came down in average
    on 42,9%,and the level of tyronyn on 7,5%.After doing the pose of Lotos a little
    oppressing influence was found out,the level of tyroxyn came down in average on
    0,5-0,7%,tryiodtyronyn almost didn&quot;t change.The same picture after doing the poses
    for twisting the spine.</font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2">The reaction to the set on shoulder-blades doesn&quot;t
    conform with the literature facts.Facts given by some of the authors say that this pose
    stimulates the activity of the thyroid gland,our results show a little (0,1-0,4%)
    oppressing influence on this organ.The conformation of this fact is that the level of the
    tyreotropical hormon,which stimulates the activity of the thyroid gland, increases from 0
    to 0,95 пm/l only while doing this pose.</font></p>
    <p style="text-indent: 40; text-align: justify"><font size="2">So, such a conclusion can be made:all the investigated
    poses have an influence on the activity of the thyroid gland,stimulating or oppressing its
    function and this fact should be taken into account while doing the exercises by the
    method of yoga.</font></td>
  </tr>
</table>
</body>
